HEADWORD: Tump
<hw>Tump</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucr⟧mp)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[W.
<ets>twmp</ets>, <ets>twm</ets>, a round mass or heap, a hillock.]</ety>
<def>A little hillock; a knoll.</def> <rj><au>Ainsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tump</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tump
<hw>Tump</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Tumped</conjf> <pr>(t⟦ucr⟧mt; 215)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Tumping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To form a
mass of earth or a hillock about; <as>as, to <ex>tump</ex>
teasel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To draw or drag, as a deer or other animal after it
has been killed.</def> <mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

